ProtoTheorem:
. "Let $C = \langle g(t) \rangle$ be a cyclic code in $R_n$ 
   and suppose that $\omega$ is a primitive $n$th root of unity
   over ${\mathbb Z}_2$. If $s$ consecutive powers of $\omega$ 
   are roots of $g(x)$, then the minimum distance of $C$ is at 
   least $s+1$."
